The paper deals with the problem of detecting and localizing angiodysplasia lesions in gastrointestinal tract images using deep convolutional neural networks. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also involves image processing and analysis (cs.MM) and medical imaging (cs.IR).
